The Abia State government has promised to give N5m to anyone with actionable information on the abductors of Prof. Uwadinachi Iweha, a former Chief Medical Officer (CMD) of Abia State University Teaching Hospital (ABSUTH), Aba. Prof. Iweha was kidnapped at his residence in Umuopara, Umuahia South LGA by unknown gunmen. Members of the Nigerian Medical Association (NMA) have threatened to down tools indefinitely until their colleague is freed.   Kwara records first monkey pox case     Terrorist killed, weapons recovered in Kaduna      Cocaine smuggling: Court orders interim forfeiture of…   In a statement by the Secretary to the State Government (SSG), Chris Ezem, the state government said it was making every effort to ensure Dr Iweha is released. “Government is offering a handsome reward of the sum of Five Million Naira (N5m) to any one or group with useful information that will lead to the rescue of Prof. Iweha from his abductors,and or the arrest of the abductors. “Government will continue to discharge its responsibility of securing the lives and properties of all Abians and residents in the State, and advise all to be security conscious and report any suspicious movement in and around them to security agents. “The security and welfare of residents of the state remains Paramount to this Administration.”